cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software, please cite both this repository and the parent research program's pre-registration (OSF DOI 10.17605/OSF.IO/Q6JYN)."
title: "micro-kiki: 35 Domain-Expert LoRA Adapters with Cognitive Layer on Qwen3.5 MoE"
abstract: >
  micro-kiki is a deployable 3B-active MoE-LoRA instantiation of the
  dreamOfkiki framework. It pairs 35 domain-expert LoRA adapters
  (sequentially trained via MLX on Mac Studio M3 Ultra 512 GB) with
  a router of 35 sigmoid outputs (domains are not mutually
  exclusive). Inference targets Q4_K_M quantization on consumer GPUs
  (RTX 4090 24 GB class). The cognitive layer implements a subset of
  the canonical dream operations (replay, downscale) against the
  shared episodic-memory protocol defined in the parent framework.
